It’s actually really interesting, a lot of stuff we see in pictures of space isn’t actually visible to the eye. The light from certain objects are in wavelengths that we cannot see. Telescopes like Hubble and other ones pick up on those different wavelengths and “stacks” them together into one image that then contains something we can see
4:21 AM
